his is why the world needs this,\\\" said American B-Girl Logistx, also known as Logan Edra.\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 2012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997018399416, \"rank\": 1.9920623054638967e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking originated as part of hip-hop culture in New York in the 1970s.\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2064, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999885376384, \"rank\": 8.134799973048418e-09, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What began in the block parties of the Bronx has reached the fountains and classical facades of one of Paris's most opulent public spaces, overseen by the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 0.9999984454405682, \"rank\": 1.5538300043787642e-06, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 2191, \"end\": 2196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.657236239580531e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"